Package: LDxBlocks
Type: Package
Title: Genome-Wide LD Block Detection and Haplotype Analysis (r² and rV², C++ Accelerated)
Version: 0.3.0
Date: 2025-04-07
Authors@R:
    person(
      given   = "Félicien",
      family  = "Akohoue",
      email   = "akohoue.f@gmail.com",
      role    = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2160-0182")
    )
Description: Fast, scalable linkage disequilibrium (LD) block detection for
    genome-wide SNP data. Supports two LD metrics: standard r² (fast, suitable
    for 10M+ markers) and the kinship-adjusted rV² (Kim et al. 2018, GENETICS)
    for structured or related populations. The clique-based Big-LD segmentation
    algorithm is accelerated throughout by Rcpp/RcppArmadillo and OpenMP. A
    unified multi-format I/O layer reads numeric dosage CSV, HapMap, VCF,
    SeqArray GDS, and PLINK BED files. Downstream modules cover haplotype
    reconstruction, diversity metrics (richness, expected heterozygosity,
    Shannon entropy), haplotype feature matrices for genomic prediction, and
    automatic parameter tuning against GWAS marker coverage.
